  "description": "Solanaceae herb domesticated in Mexico 6,000+ years ago. Produces bell, chili, and sweet pepper morphotypes via selection on capsaicinoid biosynthesis, fruit morphology, and wall thickness. Staminate anthers release pollen via gravity and insect vibration; self-compatible but reliant on insect pollination for high fruit set.",
